(My mistake for not reading fine print).
But what really ticked me off is the charge you to cancel.
I moved to another state and when I tried to cancel on the phone, they told I needed to have a certified letter sent or they wouldn't let me cancel.
Who has time to go to the post office to cancel a $15/month membership??
Just ridiculous.
You know that saying, "you get what you pay for?
" - Well I recommend spending a bit more money and finding a gym that will work with you and not try to steal every last dollar from their customers.
I hope this review deters anyone considering this shady business.

